The Devin MCP server is an official authenticated service that provides AI agents and IDEs with programmatic access to the Devin platform, including sessions, playbooks, knowledge, schedules, and repository management [1].

To use it, connect your MCP-compatible client to the base server URL `https://mcp.devin.ai/mcp` using a service user API key (prefix `cog_`) [1]. If using an enterprise or personal access token, you must include an `X-Org-Id` header to target the correct organization [1]. 

Example configuration for an MCP client:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "devin": {
      "url": "https://mcp.devin.ai/mcp",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer cog_your_key_here",
        "X-Org-Id": "your_org_id"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
Note that the field name for the server URL varies by client, commonly `url` or `serverUrl` [1]. Legacy API keys (prefix `apk_` or `apk_user_`) are not supported [1].
